 information for James Brokenshire","1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-03-08","Passports: Republic of Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many passport applications from residents of the Republic of Ireland were processed through the Belfast Passport Office between 31 March 2014 and 31 March 2015.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","30175"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458569","Home Office","false","2016-03-14","<p>The Home Office does not disclose country specific information regarding deportation of foreign national offenders as its disclosure could prejudice relations between the UK and foreign governments.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","30211","2016-03-14T15:48:32.297Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458569/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458569/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458569/answer","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458569/answer/previousversion/50868","Biography information for James Brokenshire","1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-03-08","Deportation: Vietnam","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many removals of former, unaccompanied asylum-seeking children to Vietnam in the last three years were for offences relating to (a) drugs, (b) prostitution and (c) people trafficking.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","30210"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458570","Home Office","false","2016-03-14","<p>The Home Office does not disclose country specific information regarding deportation of foreign national offenders as its disclosure could prejudice relations between the UK and foreign governments.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","30210","2016-03-14T15:48:32.25Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458570/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458570/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458570/answer","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458570/answer/previousversion/50869","Biography information for James Brokenshire","1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-03-08","Deportation: Vietnam","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many former, unaccompanied asylum-seeking children who were removed to Vietnam in the last three years were also classified as foreign national prisoners.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","30211"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458571","Home Office","false","2016-03-17","<p>Home Office records indicate that the number of former unaccompanied asylum-seeking children removed to Vietnam between 1 January 2007 and 31 December 2015, is as shown in the following table:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Total Removed to Vietnam</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2007</p></td><td><p>30</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2008</p></td><td><p>30</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2009</p></td><td><p>20</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010</p></td><td><p>10</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011</p></td><td><p>Less than 10</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>Less than 10</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>Less than 10</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>Less than 10</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015</p></td><td><p>Less than 10</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Note: This is provisional management information that is subject to change. It has not been assured to the standard of Official Statistics. Number of removals to Vietnam have been rounded to the nearest ten.</p><p>Removal of former unaccompanied asylum seeking children will only take place after their asylum claim has been finally determined, including any appeal hearing, and it has been established that there is no risk of persecution, or of a breach of the European Convention on Human Rights, upon return to their Home Country. After a former unaccompanied asylum seeking child is over eighteen years of age, and found not to be at risk upon return to their home country, their removal will be managed in line with our usual arrangements for the safe and secure return of failed asylum seekers who do not leave the UK voluntarily.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2016-03-17T12:07:00.147Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458571/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458571/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458571/answer","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458571/answer/previousversion/50870","Biography information for James Brokenshire","1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-03-08","Deportation: Vietnam","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many former, unaccompanied asylum-seeking children were removed to Vietnam in each year between 2007 and 2015.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","30212"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458572","Home Office","false","2016-03-11","<p>Home Office officials work closely with the Independent Police Complaints Commission (IPCC) to monitor how they are delivering their objectives. The IPCC provide regular performance information to the Home Office, including information on the timeliness of completed cases, which are scrutinised closely by my officials as part of the business and corporate planning process. The Home office is working with the IPCC to develop appropriate performance measures for 2016-17, including more streamlined public access to IPCC timeliness information.</p><p>On 7 March, the Home Secretary announced plans to reform the IPCC’s Governance, to make it more effective and more responsive to the public. These plans were published on the gov.uk website: https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/reforming-the-independent-police-complaints-commission-structure-and-governance We continue to provide additional funding to support the IPCC to expand to deliver an increased volume of timely, high quality investigations. I will ask the IPCC to write to the Honourable Member in response to the request for average times to complete the complaints process, and will ask for this response to be made available in the House Library.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning","30202","2016-03-11T14:30:33.123Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458572/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458572/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458572/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-03-08","Police: Complaints","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what steps her Department is taking to reduce the time taken by the Independent Police Complaints Commission to resolve complaints.","false","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr   Poulter","30201"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458573","Home Office","false","2016-03-11","<p>Home Office officials work closely with the Independent Police Complaints Commission (IPCC) to monitor how they are delivering their objectives. The IPCC provide regular performance information to the Home Office, including information on the timeliness of completed cases, which are scrutinised closely by my officials as part of the business and corporate planning process. The Home office is working with the IPCC to develop appropriate performance measures for 2016-17, including more streamlined public access to IPCC timeliness information.</p><p>On 7 March, the Home Secretary announced plans to reform the IPCC’s Governance, to make it more effective and more responsive to the public. These plans were published on the gov.uk website: https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/reforming-the-independent-police-complaints-commission-structure-and-governance We continue to provide additional funding to support the IPCC to expand to deliver an increased volume of timely, high quality investigations. I will ask the IPCC to write to the Honourable Member in response to the request for average times to complete the complaints process, and will ask for this response to be made available in the House Library.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning","30201","2016-03-11T14:30:33.06Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458573/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458573/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458573/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-03-08","Independent Police Complaints Commission","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what average time was taken by the Independent Police Complaints Commission to complete its complaints process in each year since 2005.","false","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr   Poulter","30202"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458574","House of Commons Commission","false","2016-03-22","<p>Under the Code of Conduct for Members of Parliament, Members are personally responsible and accountable for the way they use resources provided at public expense. The House of Commons provides each Member with prepaid envelopes and stationery up to a value of £9,000 a year. In addition, specific rules on prepaid envelopes, available via the Members’ Handbook, preclude their use for communications within Parliament, or for circulars or business, personal or party political purposes. The Parliamentary Commissioner for Standards is responsible for enforcing the rules on the proper use of prepaid envelopes and stationery.</p>","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake",,"2016-03-22T16:53:04.947Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458574/answer","Biography information for Tom Brake","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458574/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458574/answer",,,,,"18","House of Commons Commission","House of Commons Commission","2016-03-08","Members: Correspondence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Rt. hon. Member for Carshalton and Wallington representing the House of Commons Commission, what steps the Commission is taking to ensure that Members of Parliament are providing good value for money in communications to their constituents using franked House of Commons envelopes.","false","Biography information for Royston Smith","Southampton, Itchen","Royston Smith","30142"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458575","Department for International Development","false","2016-03-11","<p>DFID does not have a Memorandum of Understanding with the Ministry of Defence on International Humanitarian Law.</p><p> </p>","New Forest West","Mr Desmond Swayne",,"2016-03-11T13:35:23.39Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458575/answer","Biography information for Sir Desmond Swayne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458575/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458575/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-03-08","International Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, if she will publish the memoranda of understanding between her Department and the Ministry of Defence on international humanitarian law.","false","Biography information for Stephen Doughty","Cardiff South and Penarth","Stephen Doughty","30170"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458576","Department for International Development","false","2016-03-11","<p>UK military forces operating in the Eastern Mediterranean are subject to rules of engagement which ensure compliance with international law. DFID does not in general issue guidance on international humanitarian law.</p>","New Forest West","Mr Desmond Swayne",,"2016-03-11T13:35:31.877Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458576/answer","Biography information for Sir Desmond Swayne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458576/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458576/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-03-08","Mediterranean Region: International Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what guidance her Department has issued to the (a) Ministry of Defence and (b) Home Office on international humanitarian law on UK operations in the Mediterranean.","false","Biography information for Stephen Doughty","Cardiff South and Penarth","Stephen Doughty","30169"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458577","Department for International Development","false","2016-03-14","<p>To date, the UK has committed £79.5 million to the humanitarian crisis in Iraq. This assistance is reaching hundreds of thousands of people across Iraq, including the most vulnerable groups, such as Yazidis. All UK-funded aid is distributed on the basis of need, regardless of race, religion and ethnicity.</p><p> </p><p>The UK is the largest donor to the Iraq Humanitarian Pooled Fund which, amongst other projects, has funded specialist protection and rehabilitation for escapees of Daesh terror in Iraq.</p>","New Forest West","Mr Desmond Swayne",,"2016-03-14T12:40:13.207Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458577/answer","Biography information for Sir Desmond Swayne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458577/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458577/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-03-08","Islamic State: Yazidis","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what support the Government is providing for Yazidi women who have been enslaved by Daesh; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Helen Jones","Warrington North","Helen Jones","30266"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458578","Department for International Development","false","2016-03-14","<p>DFID has 88 Senior Civil Servants (SCS) of which 45 (51%) are based in London. DFID has 225 roles designated as having a policy element of which 139 (62%) are based in London.</p>","New Forest West","Mr Desmond Swayne",,"2016-03-14T16:05:30.797Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458578/answer","Biography information for Sir Desmond Swayne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458578/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458578/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-03-08","Department for International Development: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what proportion of her Department's (a) Senior Civil Servants and (b) core policy civil servants are based in London.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","30313"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458579","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-03-15","<p>The information requested is not held centrally.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2016-03-15T14:14:33.96Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458579/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458579/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458579/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-03-08","Family Courts: Crime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many criminal offences were committed on family court premises in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Bridget Phillipson","Houghton and Sunderland South","Bridget Phillipson","30270"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458580","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-03-15","<p>Safe areas are available for vulnerable victims and witnesses at every venue where the Family Court routinely conducts hearings.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2016-03-15T14:23:20.95Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458580/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458580/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458580/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-03-08","Family Courts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, which family courts have a designated safe space for victims of domestic abuse and other vulnerable individuals.","false","Biography information for Bridget Phillipson","Houghton and Sunderland South","Bridget Phillipson","30265"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458581","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-03-11","<p>My Department has evaluated the <em>Choice not Chance</em> campaign which ran in England and Wales during March 2015 with the aim of promoting the use of wills, lasting powers of attorney and organ donation. We consider the campaign was successful in promoting the making of wills. We were unable to obtain figures for wills made during the campaign but the campaign page on gov.uk received 3,515 views and 19 campaign tweets resulted in 1,268 “click throughs” for more information. Further, the question of making a will is often considered at the same time as the question of making a lasting power of attorney. During the campaign 35,525 lasting powers were made (a 42% increase over the corresponding period in 2014) and 85,743 people accessed the online LPA tool (a 66% increase in average page views compared to the previous 6 months). A further success is that our campaign materials continue to be used by practitioners.</p><p> </p><p>The law of succession in Northern Ireland is devolved.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"2016-03-11T14:30:34.9Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458581/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458581/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458581/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-03-08","Wills","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how he plans to assess the effectiveness of the recent campaign to encourage people to make a will.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","30178"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458582","Prime Minister","false","2016-03-15","<p>President Hollande and I discussed our shared interest in building on our strong bilateral defence co-operation, but on this occasion, did not discuss nuclear weapons issues in any detail.</p>","Witney","Mr David Cameron",,"2016-03-15T17:06:23.077Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458582/answer","Biography information for Mr David Cameron","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458582/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458582/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2016-03-08","Nuclear Weapons","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, what discussions he had with the President of the French Republic on Anglo-French co-operation on nuclear weapons during his visit to France on 3 March 2016.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","30144"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458583","Prime Minister","false","2016-03-15","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave to him on 7 March 2016, UIN 29278, and to the evidence given by the Cabinet Secretary to the Public Administration and Constitutional Affairs Committee on 1 March 2016, a transcript of which can be found on the Committee’s website.</p>","Witney","Mr David Cameron","30277","2016-03-15T17:10:24.477Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458583/answer","Biography information for Mr David Cameron","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458583/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458583/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2016-03-08","UK Membership of EU: Referendums","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, if he will issue guidance on whether junior government ministers who are in favour of UK membership of the EU are to be allowed full access to documents in situations where the departmental Secretary of State is in favour of the UK leaving the EU.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","30280"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458584","Prime Minister","false","2016-03-15","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave to him on 7 March 2016, UIN 29278, and to the evidence given by the Cabinet Secretary to the Public Administration and Constitutional Affairs Committee on 1 March 2016, a transcript of which can be found on the Committee’s website.</p>","Witney","Mr David Cameron","30280","2016-03-15T17:10:24.417Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458584/answer","Biography information for Mr David Cameron","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458584/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458584/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2016-03-08","UK Membership of EU: Referendums","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, if he will issue guidance to civil servants on how to proceed in cases where departmental ministers have yet to declare a position on the referendum on the EU on their access to the upcoming departmental resources documentation relating to that referendum.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","30277"
