"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458588","Speaker's Committee for the Independent Parliamentary Standards Authority","false","2016-03-11","<p>As at 9 March 2016, 3,161 individuals were employed by MPs and paid through IPSA’s payroll. Of these, 1795 were female and 1366 were male.</p><p>IPSA does not collect or hold data on the ethnicity of MPs’ staff.</p>","Broxbourne","Mr Charles Walker",,"2016-03-11T11:20:33.563Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458588/answer","Biography information for Sir Charles Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458588/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458588/answer",,,,,"90","Speaker's Committee for the Independent Parliamentary Standards Authority","Speaker's Committee for the Independent Parliamentary Standards Authority","2016-03-08","Members' Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the hon. Member for Broxbourne, representing the Speaker's Committee for the Independent Parliamentary Standards Authority, what the (a) ethnicity and (b) gender is of each staff member employed by hon. Members.","false","Biography information for Royston Smith","Southampton, Itchen","Royston Smith","30271"
