"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458604","Department for Transport","false","2016-03-16","<p>89% of Senior Civil Servants in the Department for Transport are based in London.</p><p> </p><p>Information on the profession of civil servants is not stored on the central system and therefore we are unable to confirm which civil servants who define themselves as a Policy professional are based in London.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2016-03-16T09:50:58.107Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458604/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458604/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458604/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-03-08","Department for Transport: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what proportion of his Department's (a) Senior Civil Servants and (b) core policy civil servants are based in London.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","30315"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458605","Department for Transport","false","2016-03-15","<p>The Secretary of State has accepted Govia Thameslink Railway’s Remedial Plan that sets out the steps the operator is taking to improve their performance and it will shortly be published on the Government’s website. The plan covers the period to September 2018.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry","30345","2016-03-15T16:45:42.107Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458605/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458605/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458605/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-03-08","Govia Thameslink Railway","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what deadline Govia Thameslink Railway Ltd has been set to meet the terms of its Remedial Plan.","false","Biography information for Richard Fuller","Bedford","Richard Fuller","30379"
